The White House Internship Program for Spring 2018 is now accepting applications. The deadline for applications is September 8, 2017. The program will run from January 10 to April 27, 2018. Applicants must be at least 18 years old, U.S. citizens, and meet certain criteria such as being enrolled in or having graduated from a degree program, or being a veteran of the U.S. Armed Forces. The selection process is competitive and based on demonstrated commitment to public service, leadership, and commitment to the Trump Administration. For more information and application details, visit the White House website.